name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: mapreduce.job.ubertask.maxreduces
description:
Threshold for number of reduces, beyond which job is considered
  too big for the ubertasking optimization.  CURRENTLY THE CODE CANNOT SUPPORT
  MORE THAN ONE REDUCE and will ignore larger values.  (Zero is a valid max,
  however.)  Users may override this value, but only downward.

name: ha.zookeeper.session-timeout.ms
description:
The session timeout to use when the ZKFC connects to ZooKeeper.
    Setting this value to a lower value implies that server crashes
    will be detected more quickly, but risks triggering failover too
    aggressively in the case of a transient error or network blip.

name: ha.failover-controller.graceful-fence.rpc-timeout.ms
description: Timeout that the FC waits for the old active to go to standby

name: mapreduce.reduce.cpu.vcores
description:
The number of virtual cores to request from the scheduler for
  each reduce task.

name: dfs.namenode.decommission.blocks.per.interval
description:
The approximate number of blocks to process per decommission
    or maintenance interval, as defined in dfs.namenode.decommission.interval.

name: dfs.qjournal.new-epoch.timeout.ms
description:
Timeout in milliseconds when getting an epoch number for write
    access to JournalNodes.
